laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 1.9 cm and is fluid filled. There is surrounding periappendiceal fat stranding and an appendicolith within the proximal portion of the appendix. No extraluminal free air is identified in the region to suggest microperforation. The kidneys appear symmetric without focal lesion. The liver, spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands are normal. No abdominal free fluid or free air is evident. The rectum and colon are normal in caliber and configuration without evidence of obstruction or inflammation. The bladder is mildly distended and appears unremarkable.
